<span class="displaytext"><b>for immediate release</b> <br/> <b>contact:</b> kevin madden (857) 288-6390 <p><b>boston, ma</b> - (candidate last) for president today announced a major new feature of mitt(candidate last).com –"five brothers," the (candidate last) campaign blog – and that governor (candidate full) is participating in two new online initiatives. these new online tools allow the american people to interact directly with governor (candidate last) and members of the (candidate last) family. </p><p>these innovative, new-media technologies all offer unprecedented opportunities for voters to share their views and ideas with governor (candidate last) while learning about his vision for meeting the new generation of challenges facing our nation. </p><p>the new interactive features include: "five brothers," the (candidate last) campaign blog, the you choose '08 spotlight on youtube, and yahoo! answers. </p><p><b> <u>"five brothers," the (candidate last) campaign blog:</u> </b> </p><p>launched this morning by governor (candidate last)'s five sons - tagg, ben, josh, craig and matt - "five brothers" will feature the brothers' posts, video and photos from the campaign trail. governor and mrs. (candidate last) will occasionally contribute as well. supporters are encouraged to comment, share their thoughts and discuss the campaign. </p><p><em>to view "five brothers" and watch tagg (candidate last)'s video introduction, please visit</em>: <a href="http://fivebrothers.(candidate full).com">http://fivebrothers.(candidate full).com</a> </p><p><b> <u>you choose '08 spotlight on youtube:</u> </b> </p><p>governor (candidate last) is the first 2008 presidential candidate to participate in the you choose '08 spotlight in a completely unprecedented use of video on the web. rarely do presidential candidates have the chance to communicate with such a large number of voters and directly solicit their ideas and input. governor (candidate last) is using his week in the spotlight to ask the youtube community what they believe is the single greatest challenge facing america and what they would do about it. by the end of his spotlighted week, governor (candidate last) will record additional web videos with his thoughts on the numerous video responses that are already being submitted. </p><p><em>to view governor (candidate last)'s video and post your response, please visit</em>: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/(candidate full)">http://www.youtube.com/(candidate full)</a> </p><p><u> <b>yahoo! answers:</b> <br/> </u> <br/>in anticipation of tax day, governor (candidate last) has partnered with yahoo! to ask the yahoo! answers community how they would change the tax code to ease the burden on families and promote growth and innovation. governor (candidate last)'s question, coupled with a video on his tax philosophy, has been featured on the homepage of yahoo!, the most visited web site on the internet, and will receive thousands - if not tens of thousands - of answers. </p><p><em>to answer governor (candidate last)'s question and offer your opinion, please visit</em>: <a href="http://answers.yahoo.com/question/index?qid=20070410092341aaxnl7b">http://answers.yahoo.com/question/index?qid=20070410092341aaxnl7b</a></p></span>



